</table>

<h1>2. Module Implementation</h1>

<h2>2.1 Authentication & Profile Module</h2>
<p>Implemented in <code>src/context/AuthContext.tsx</code> and <code>src/supabase.ts</code>. Supports dual-mode authentication. In live cloud mode, user authentication is managed by Supabase Auth (<code>supabase.auth.signInWithPassword</code>). In demo or offline fallback mode, user state resolves against local storage collections (<code>kobowise_profiles</code>).</p>

<pre>
const login = async (email: string, password: string) => {
  setLoading(true);
  try {
    const isDemoEmail = email.includes('buyer@delsu.edu') || email.includes('trader@delsu.edu');
    if (isDemoMode || isDemoEmail) {
      initializeMockDb();
      const profiles = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('kobowise_profiles') || '[]');
      const cleanEmail = email.trim().toLowerCase();
      let profile = profiles.find((p: any) => p.email && p.email.toLowerCase() === cleanEmail) || null;
      if (profile) {
        setUser(profile);
        localStorage.setItem('kobowise_session_user', profile.id);
        return { success: true };
      }
    } else {
      const { data, error } = await supabase!.auth.signInWithPassword({ email, password });
      if (error) throw error;
      if (data.user) {
        const profile = await dbService.getProfile(data.user.id);
        if (profile) setUser({ ...profile, email: data.user.email });
        return { success: true };
      }
    }
  } finally {
    setLoading(false);
  }
};
</pre>

<h2>2.2 Product Catalog & Search Module</h2>
<p>Implemented across <code>src/pages/Home.tsx</code>, <code>src/pages/Browse.tsx</code>, and <code>src/components/ProductCard.tsx</code>. Renders active bulk products displaying total bulk price (e.g. ₦72,000 for 50kg Rice), split portion shares (e.g. 4 shares at ₦18,000/share), real-time progress bars (<code>shares_purchased / shares_needed</code>), and campus pickup locations in Abraka.</p>

<h2>2.3 Group Buy Pooling Engine</h2>
<p>Implemented in <code>src/supabase.ts</code> (<code>buyShares</code> method). Executes an atomic transaction upon purchase:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Increments <code>shares_purchased</code> on active <code>group_orders</code> record.</li>
  <li>When <code>shares_purchased >= shares_needed</code>, sets status to <code>'completed'</code>, decrements product <code>stock_quantity</code>, and dispatches vendor notifications.</li>
  <li>Spawns a new pending group buy slot if stock remains.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2.4 Cart & Payment Integration</h2>
<p>Implemented in <code>src/context/CartContext.tsx</code> and <code>src/pages/Checkout.tsx</code>. Aggregates multi-item portion shares, adds a flat ₦200 campus delivery coordination fee, generates unique payment reference codes (e.g., <code>KBW-1721839401</code>), and integrates Paystack inline gateway checkout.</p>

<h2>2.5 Trader Fulfillment Dashboard</h2>
<p>Implemented in <code>src/pages/TraderDashboard.tsx</code> and <code>src/supabase.ts</code> (<code>getTraderOrders</code>). Provides merchants with store revenue analytics, inventory management tools, low stock alerts, and fulfillment action triggers (<em>Confirm Order</em> → <em>Mark Delivered</em> → <em>Approve Refund</em>).</p>

<h2>2.6 Hybrid Data Access Layer (<code>dbService</code>)</h2>
<p>Implemented in <code>src/supabase.ts</code>. Operates a dual-source reader/writer pattern: queries Supabase PostgreSQL and merges local browser <code>localStorage</code> records using Map data structures, guaranteeing zero data loss during network instability.</p>

